    fix(ws-b): resolve poster URL before scheme check in Photos screens; repair skipped/vacuous resolveUrl tests

    Photos screens (PhotoAlbumScreen, PhotosScreen) scheme-checked the RAW
    posterUrl before resolveUrl(), dropping all relative thumbnails. Resolve
    first, then scheme-check, then pass the resolved URL to the loader —
    mirroring DetailScreen. Unskip/rewrite the SearchScreen resolveUrl tests
    (masked a test-harness flaw, not a prod bug) and rewrite the vacuous
    DetailScreen/BrowseScreen child-poster tests to genuinely exercise URL
    resolution (real local HTTP server for the relative case; deterministic
    scheduled-load-count for empty/malformed/non-http). Add topLevel=1
    assertion to MediaQueryTest::testForLibrary.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
